headline: You Think Tesla Sales Are Weak Now? Just Wait.
summary: The U.S. electric-vehicle industry has a looming problem that has nothing to do with politics or  Tesla  CEO Elon Musk.  Americans bought 310,839 EVs in the second quarter of 2025, down 6% year over year.  Tesla sales dropped almost 13% to 143,535 vehicles.

headline: EV Deals Are Booming Ahead of Tax-Credit Expiration
summary: DENVER—At a  Kia  dealership here on the city’s south side, a steady stream of shoppers navigate around noisy renovation work in search of electric vehicles with supercheap lease deals.  As of last week, Emich Kia offered to lease the small Niro EV for $40 a month before taxes.  The EV6 lease was being marketed for less than $100 a month, while a $65,000 three-row EV9 could be had for $189 a month before taxes.
